description.text:
Added new functions to the Image class to handle resizing an image to a lower resolution.
`
int Image.get_original_width() const;
int Image.get_original_height() const;
Size2i Image.get_original_size() const;
Image.PerformanceMode Image.get_performance_mode() const;
Error Image.set_performance_mode();
`
The `*_original_*` functions will return the values that the image had before calling `set_performance_mode()`.

 Inside the ProjectSettings are a few new options that controls what the engine does when loading a CompressedTexture2D from disk. There are three modes of operation. The default, "Original Size" option does not resize textures. The "Max Size" option will resize all textures to fit into a defined size if they are bigger then that size. The last option, "Downscale Factor" will resize all textures logarithmically.

If resizing is not desired for selected textures, an option in the import dock has been added that, when enabled, will prevent the engine from resizing any given texture
